### Rules — do not change these

- The line (loader-track) is ALWAYS full width — it is the 
  track/rail. Only the dot moves along it.
- The dot does NOT leave a colored trail behind it — no 
  fill animation on the track. The dot alone is the indicator.
  This is what makes it feel premium vs a Bootstrap progress bar.
- progress easing MUST use the 3-phase custom function —
  the slow phase in the middle (60→85%) is what creates 
  tension and makes 100% feel earned.
- loader-pct font-weight MUST be 300 (thin) — heavier weights 
  make the number look like a dashboard widget, not a cinematic loader.
- exitLoader() sequence must be exactly:
    inner fades (200ms) → loader fades (500ms) → DOM removed → 
    loaderComplete event fires
  Do not collapse these into one transition.

